                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12569797" author="bdelacretaz" created="Mon, 18 Feb 2008 08:19:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; I think the best way to pass Locale information to a parser is as a part of the Metadata object.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Agreed, Locale.setLocale() could be set to a Locale that has nothing to do with the documents being analyzed, so what you suggest makes sense.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12790470" author="jukkaz" created="Mon, 14 Dec 2009 23:53:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The parse context mechanism is perfect for this need. Use the following code to specify the default locale to be used when formatting data from documents like Excel sheets that don&apos;t contain explicit locale information:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Parser parser = ...;&lt;br/&gt;
    ParseContext context = new ParseContext();&lt;br/&gt;
    context.set(Locale.class, myLocale);&lt;br/&gt;
    parser.parse(..., context);&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
